HEADWORD: Freemason
<hw>Free"ma`son</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One of an ancient
and secret association or fraternity, said to have been at first
composed of masons or builders in stone, but now consisting of persons
who are united for social enjoyment and mutual assistance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Freemasonic</ent>⟦br⟧
